* [Showcase: Peruse the stalls] -> stalls

=== bees

Bees!

Main attraction: Sacred soothing honey (and wax, mead...)

Yellows and golds are the primary highlight colors for everything.

Hexagonal patterns: sleeping pods, Queenpriest.

Abuzz: crowd noise, drunkenness, lingering questions, nervousness...

* [Themes] -> themes

=== apes

Apes

A touch of exoticism.

A signpost that this is not our world.

Mandril hides, The Gliding Monkey, orangutan guard-dog, sled pulled by gorillas...

* [Themes] -> themes

=== wool

The one magical touch: anti-gravity wool, floating sheep.

A hint at agricultural surroundings.

* [Themes] -> themes

=== accord

The Accord is the religious creed at the temple.

"Accord" is also used in speech to as "I agree" or "understood".

Monks keep their wrists tied with a sacred Chord.

The Chord also is the weapon of their martial art.

Accordions: one of the key crafts, the primary source of music.

* [Themes] -> themes

=== stalls

Behind a richly gilded stall, a richly gilded man, grinning, pronounces the holiness of his wax idols.

On a floating cloud of wool, samples of rotund cheeses are given away, by a rotund farmgirl.

An old master sits on the bare stone, an old orangutan beside, guarding the delicate accordions of his craft.

* [Back to what I came for] -> descriptions

=== narrative

Framing: the beginning of the end of a long journey.

Pure description gets stale fast, a subjective perspective is very enriching:

Exploration gradually reveals: the place, the character, the mysterious goal.

I wanted to have a constant pull: pervasive hints that trigger questions.

What is this place?
Why is he here?
What is he chasing?
What's at the end?

* [Backbone Architecture] -> backbone

=== backbone

The architecture pulls the player forward and upward.

A temple-town lends itself to a vertical structure.

Three levels:

Lower District: outward facing - marketplace, inn, tent field...

Middle District: urban heart - craft, commerce, leisure, culture, education...

Upper District: holy core - hives, temple...

Stairs between districts serve as medidative breaks and narrative progression.

Opportunities for playful distraction, with a payoff at the summit.

